%20particular%20soft%20spot%20for%20Kyoto%2C%20which%20was%20the%20capital%20of%20Japan%20for%20over%20a%20thousand%20years%20until%201868%2C%20when%20Tokyo%20took%20its%20place.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20often%20thought%20of%20as%20a%20natural%20second%20city%20to%20visit%20alongside%20Tokyo%2C%20Kyoto%20is%20Cheng's%20undisputed%20No.%201%20Japanese%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20old%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecity%20is%20lined%20with%20small%20walkable%20roads%2C%20has%20many%20temples%2C%20and%20boasts%20a%20riverbank%20lined%20with%20small%20houses%20and%20shops.%20One%20of%20Kyoto's%20famous%20features%20is%20the%20Gion%20district%2C%20a%20historic%20neighborhood%20dotted%20with%20ochaya%2C%20or%20teahouses%2C%20run%20by%20traditional%20female%20entertainers%20known%20as%20geisha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20it%20is%20also%20a%20tourist%20hot%20spot%2C%20Cheng%20said%20Kyoto%20feels%20more%20serene%20than%20Tokyo.%20It's%20not%20surprising%2C%20considering%20the%20current%20Japanese%20capital's%20population%20dwarfs%20the%20former.%20The%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funstats.un.org%2Funsd%2Fdemographic-social%2Fproducts%2Fdyb%2Fdocuments%2FDYB2022%2Ftable08.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUN%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20from%202022%2C%20estimates%20Kyoto's%20population%20is%20just%20over%201.46%20million%2C%20a%20fraction%20of%20Tokyo's%209.73%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20love%20Tokyo%2C%20and%20I%20do%20as%20well%2C%20but%20I%20think%20Tokyo%20is%20kind%20of%20overrated%2C%20and%20I%20feel%20Kyoto%20has%20more%20in%20a%20cultural%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20the%20teahouses%2C%20it%20has%20the%20Gion%20district%2C%20all%20the%20temples%2C%20the%20shrines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20a%20lot%20calmer%20and%20peaceful%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20city's%20qualities%20exemplify%20%26quot%3BJapanese%20culture.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESapporo%20is%20often%20overlooked%2C%20but%20Cheng%20said%20it%20has%20the%20warmest%20locals%20and%20is%20home%20to%20one%20of%20her%20favorite%20Japanese%20dishes.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20cityscape%20of%20Sapporo%2C%20Japan%20at%20sunset%2C%20showing%20tall%20buildings%20and%20a%20long%20tree-lined%20parkway.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669e7bbe80d4d5da13d5dc70%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22899%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECheng%20says%20the%20local%20people%20of%20Sapporo%20are%20incredibly%20friendly%20and%20welcoming.%3Cp%3ESean%20Pavone%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20%26quot%3Boften%20overlook%26quot%3B%20Hokkaido%20in%20the%20north%20of%20Japan%2C%20but%20it's%20%26quot%3Bso%20beautiful%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdifferent%26quot%3B%20to%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20country%2C%20Cheng%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHokkaido's%20capital%2C%20Sapporo%2C%20is%20about%20a%2090-minute%20flight%20from%20Tokyo.%20It's%20best%20known%20for%20its%20eponymous%20locally%20brewed%20beer%20and%20its%20powdery%20ski%20slopes%20%E2%80%94%20though%20Cheng%20prefers%20it%20to%20Tokyo%20for%20its%20cuisine%2C%20cheaper%20prices%2C%20and%20welcoming%20locals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20Japanese%20are%20very%20friendly%2C%20and%20they're%20very%20polite%20and%20respectful%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20feel%20like%20up%20there%2C%20it's%20just%20a%20completely%20different%20sense%20of%20friendliness.%20They%20just%20go%20out%20of%20their%20way%2C%20and%20you%20can%20definitely%20tell%20if%20someone%20is%20from%20Tokyo%20or%20the%20north.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20dishes%20she'd%20recommend%20to%20anyone%20going%20to%20Sapporo%20is%20%26quot%3Bsoup%20curry%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20warm%20curry%20powder-%20and%20garam%20masala-spiced%20broth%20with%20chicken%20and%20fried%20vegetables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20something%20that%20was%20recommended%20to%20me%2C%20and%20I%20just%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFor%20foodies%2C%20Cheng%20said%20there's%20nowhere%20better%20to%20visit%20in%20Japan%20than%20Osaka.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20female%20hand%20holding%20a%20plate%20full%20of%20takoyaki%2C%20or%20deep-fried%20octopus%20balls%2C%20in%20the%20city%20center%20of%20Osaka.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669e7c5e2d66759f66fce8d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETakoyaki%2C%20small%20fried%20balls%20of%20octopus%2C%20are%20a%20local%20delicacy%20in%20Osaka.%3Cp%3EShih-wei%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOsaka%2C%20often%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BJapan's%20Kitchen%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20another%20city%20Cheng%20prefers%20over%20Tokyo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocated%20just%20over%20three%20hours%20away%20from%20the%20capital%20via%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Friding-japans-famous-186-mile-per-hour-bullet-train-review-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShinkansen%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20bullet%20train%2C%20the%20city%20is%20famed%20for%20its%20street%20food%20and%20bustling%20produce%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhenever%20I%20go%20there%2C%20my%20sole%20mission%20is%20to%20eat%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%20One%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20delicacies%20in%20Osaka%20is%20takoyaki%2C%20fried%20dough%20balls%20containing%20octopus%20slathered%20in%20sauces%20and%20topped%20with%20scallions%20and%20bonito%20flakes%2C%20Cheng%20said.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAnother%20dish%20Cheng%20makes%20sure%20to%20grab%20every%20time%20she's%20in%20Osaka%20is%20tonkatsu%2C%20or%20fried%20pork%20cutlet%2C%20at%20a%20restaurant%20called%20Tonkatsu%20Daiki.%20She%20said%20it's%20made%20to%20%26quot%3Bperfection%26quot%3B%20and%20served%20with%20a%20side%20of%20all-you-can-eat%20shredded%20cabbage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20usually%20a%20line%20out%20the%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20The%20tiny%20restaurant%20is%20run%20by%20one%20chef%20who%20%26quot%3Bcooks%20everything%20on%20the%20spot%2C%26quot%3B%20so%20Cheng%20recommends%20visitors%20arrive%2030%20minutes%20before%20it%20opens%20at%20lunch%20to%20improve%20their%20chances%20of%20grabbing%20a%20bite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAs%20much%20as%20Cheng%20says%20Tokyo%20is%20%26quot%3Boverrated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20still%20thinks%20all%20first-time%20tourists%20to%20Japan%20should%20go.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shibuya%20Shopping%20District%2C%20Tokyo%2C%20Japan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6615861c16bde8d4ead7044f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJapan%20is%20one%20of%20the%20safest%20countries%20Cheng%20has%20visited.%3Cp%3ERasmus%20Jurkatam%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20Tokyo%20is%20not%20one%20of%20Cheng's%20top%20three%20favorite%20cities%20in%20Japan%2C%20she%20wouldn't%20dissuade%20tourists%20from%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20saying%2C%20for%20Tokyo%2C%20it's%20a%20bit%20overrated%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20people%20want%20to%20actually%20experience%20more%20of%20Japan%2C%20then%20I%20would%20say%20go%20to%20the%20other%20cities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Cheng%20does%20visit%20Tokyo%2C%20she%20always%20stays%20in%20Ginza%2C%20a%20neighborhood%20in%20the%20center%20of%20town%20known%20for%20boulevards%20lined%20with%20designer%20stores%20and%20luxury%20hotels%2C%20as%20well%20as%20smaller%20streets%20with%20boutiques%2C%20caf%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20sushi%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20%26quot%3Byounger%20crowd%26quot%3B%20and%20those%20keen%20on%20sampling%20Tokyo's%20bustling%20nightlife%2C%20Cheng%20recommends%20staying%20in%20Shinjuku%2C%20a%20slightly%20more%20affordable%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGinza%20and%20Shinjuku%20are%20the%20main%20options%20that%20people%20always%20debate%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20Cheng%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20love%20Ginza%20because%20it's%20so%20clean%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20accessible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20Tokyo%20is%20a%20versatile%20city%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20looking%20for%20serenity%2C%20if%20you're%20looking%20for%20nightlife%2C%20it%20has%20something%20for%20everyone%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETokyo%20is%20also%20well-connected%20to%20other%20lesser-known%20travel%20destinations.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20view%20from%20Hase-dera%20Temple%20in%20Kamakura%2C%20Japan%2C%20showing%20the%20Shonan%20coastline%20and%20the%20Yuigahama%20Beach.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F669eb1882d66759f66fd0d78%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22854%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt%20only%20takes%20around%20an%20hour%20by%20train%20to%20get%20from%20Tokyo%20to%20seaside%20spots%20in%20Kamakura%2C%20Cheng%20said.%3Cp%3EToYoPHoTo%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20travelers%20don't%20have%20enough%20vacation%20time%20to%20traverse%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20them%2C%20Cheng%20recommends%20day%20trips%20using%20Tokyo%20as%20a%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20Kamakura%2C%20a%20coastal%20city%20in%20the%20Kanagawa%20prefecture%20less%20than%20an%20hour%20away%20from%20Tokyo%20by%20train%2C%20is%20worth%20checking%20out%20for%20a%20change%20of%20scenery.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Tokyo%20locals%20flock%20to%20Kamakura%20during%20the%20warmer%20seasons%20for%20its%20beaches%20and%20seaside%20restaurants.%20It's%20also%20known%20for%20its%20large%20Buddha%20statue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20