nflation-powell-economists-forecast-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterest%20rate%20cut%3C%2Fa%3E%20pretty%20soon%2C%20but%20probably%20not%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20Federal%20Open%20Market%20Committee%20will%20announce%20its%20next%20interest%20rate%20decision%2C%20and%20it's%20once%20again%20expected%20to%20hold%20rates%20steady.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME%20FedWatch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20estimates%20probabilities%20of%20interest%20rate%20changes%20based%20on%20market%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eactivity%2C%20forecasts%20a%20roughly%2095%25%20chance%20the%20Fed%20will%20not%20change%20rates%20as%20of%20Monday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20FOMC's%20September%20meeting%20could%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseptember-fed-interest-rate-cuts-soft-landing-inflation-powell-su-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebring%20Americans%20the%20relief%3C%2Fa%3E%20they've%20been%20waiting%20for%20%E2%80%94%20CME%20FedWatch%20showed%20markets%20think%20it's%20all%20but%20certain%20the%20Fed%20will%20cut%20rates%20that%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuts%20could%20be%20valuable%20for%20Americans%20struggling%20with%20high%20mortgage%20and%20credit%20card%20rates.%20Lower%20interest%20rates%20would%20make%20borrowing%20more%20affordable%20for%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed's%20high%20target%20interest%20rate%20%26quot%3Bis%20putting%20pressure%20on%20the%20economy%2C%20is%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20consumers%20to%20buy%2C%26quot%3B%20Claudia%20Sahm%2C%20chief%20economist%20at%20investment%20management%20firm%20New%20Century%20Advisors%20and%20former%20Fed%20economist%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20take%20out%20credit.%20It's%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20businesses%20to%20invest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20will%20likely%20have%20to%20wait%20a%20bit%20longer%20for%20those%20cuts%2C%20however.%20%26quot%3BA%20July%20Federal%20Reserve%20interest%20rate%20cut%20is%20unlikely%20but%20it%20will%20be%20debated%20and%20the%20decision%20second-guessed%20if%20we%20see%20weakening%20economic%20data%20over%20the%20next%20month%20or%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Greg%20McBride%2C%20Bankrate's%20chief%20financial%20analyst%2C%20said%20in%20written%20commentary.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Fed%20will%20instead%20guide%20expectations%20toward%20a%20September%20rate%20move%2C%20pending%20continued%20improvement%20on%20the%20inflation%20front.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20released%20in%20July%20showed%20inflation%20continued%20to%20slow%20down.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cpi-june-prices-food-energy-fed-interest-rate-cuts-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20increased%203.0%25%20for%20the%2012%20months%20ending%20June%2C%20a%20cooler%20rate%20than%20the%203.3%25%20in%20May.%20The%20Personal%20Consumption%20Expenditures%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bea.gov%2Fdata%2Fpersonal-consumption-expenditures-price-index%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprice%20index%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20showed%20how%20inflation%20is%20getting%20closer%20to%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20target.%20The%20year-over-year%20increase%20for%20this%20inflation%20indicator%20was%202.5%25%2C%20just%20slightly%20cooler%20than%20the%202.6%25%20rise%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20been%20a%20rebalancing%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployment-rate-job-growth-june-economic-data-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Monthly%20job%20gains%20have%20been%20under%20300%2C000%20this%20year%2C%20except%20for%20the%20310%2C000%20in%20March.%20Plus%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgdp-gross-domestic-product-second-quarter-2024-us-economy-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20GDP%20surged%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20an%20annualized%20rate%20of%202.8%25%20in%20the%20year's%20second%20quarter%2C%20far%20above%20the%201.4%25%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%20Those%20numbers%20all%20point%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseptember-fed-interest-rate-cuts-soft-landing-inflation-powell-su-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20soft%20landing%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Fed%20is%20looking%20for%2C%20during%20which%20the%20central%20bank%20can%20fight%20inflation%20while%20avoiding%20a%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20has%20shown%20the%20economy%20is%20moving%20in%20the%20right%20direction%2C%20inching%20toward%20the%20Fed's%202%25%20inflation%20target.%20Still%2C%20Fed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20has%20been%20clear%20that%20he%20does%20not%20want%20the%20central%20bank%20to%20move%20too%20quickly%20and%20cut%20rates%20too%20soon%2C%20running%20the%20risk%20of%20having%20to%20hike%20rates%20again%20at%20a%20later%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20we%20loosen%20policy%20too%20late%20or%20too%20little%2C%20we%20could%20hurt%20economic%20activity%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said%20before%20the%20Senate%20Committee%20on%20Banking%2C%20Housing%2C%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20on%20July%209.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20loosen%20policy%20too%20much%20or%20too%20soon%2C%20then%20we%20could%20undermine%20the%20progress%20on%20inflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20economists%20and%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20have%20been%20urging%20the%20Fed%20to%20cut%20rates%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%20given%20the%20economic%20progress%20the%20country%20has%20made.%20Sahm%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20have%20seen%20the%20US%20economy%20has%20been%20getting%20back%20on%20track%2C%20normalizing%2C%20rebalancing%2C%20all%20of%20the%20Fed's%20catchwords%20for%20some%20time%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite