ce-returning-home-linkedin-poll-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrab%20a%20coffee%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20complete%20their%20work%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20are%20people%20doing%20this%3F%20Well%2C%20often%20because%20there's%20no%20great%20rationale%20for%20why%20they%20need%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20actually%20more%20productive%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20have%20asked%20employees%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floud-quitting-job-rto-policy-bad-company-culture-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20remote%20work%20spread%20across%20tech%20and%20corporate%20America%20(and%20the%20world)%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20for%20some%20workplaces%2C%20this%20makes%20sense.%20Being%20in%20the%20same%20place%20with%20fellow%20team%20members%20may%20lead%20to%20more%20collaboration%20and%20stronger%20relationships.%20Early%20career%20employees%20may%20benefit%20from%20being%20in%20person%20with%20more%20tenured%20colleagues%20and%20their%20managers%2C%20which%20provides%20more%20opportunities%20for%20mentoring%2C%20coaching%2C%20and%20feedback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20isn't%20the%20reality%20for%20many%20employees%20who%20find%20themselves%20%26quot%3Bcoffee%20badging.%26quot%3B%20Instead%2C%20they%20may%20find%20themselves%20sitting%20in%20an%20office%20on%20Zoom%20calls%20that%20they%20could%20have%20taken%20from%20home%2C%20or%20distracted%20by%20the%20busyness%20of%20the%20office%20leaving%20them%20to%20catch%20up%20after%20work%20when%20they%20get%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20my%20take%3A%20Bring%20it%20on.%20If%20there's%20not%20a%20good%20reason%20for%20employees%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20employers%20should%20be%20surprised%20when%20they%20opt%20to%20stay%20home.%20Better%20yet%2C%20take%20steps%20to%20make%20coffee%20badging%20unnecessary%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20workplace%20is%20constantly%20changing%20alongside%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20Fifty%20years%20ago%2C%20remote%20work%20didn't%20exist.%20Today%2C%20there%20are%20entire%20companies%20worth%20billions%20that%20are%20remote-first%20and%20have%20no%20offices%20(for%20example%2C%20the%20automation%20company%20where%20I%20work%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fzapier.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZapier%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20event%20management%20platform%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhopin.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHopin%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Modern%20tools%20make%20it%20possible%20for%20people%20to%20collaborate%20and%20be%20even%20more%20productive%20without%20ever%20leaving%20their%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20employees%20found%20the%20office%20to%20be%20a%20place%20that%20enabled%20them%20to%20be%20more%20productive%20and%20do%20great%20work%2C%20they%20would%20likely%20go%20in.%20If%20there%20are%20purposeful%20reasons%20for%20an%20employee%20to%20be%20in%20an%20office%2C%20then%20employers%20should%20require%20them%20to%20be%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20it's%20simply%20a%20requirement%20without%20any%20real%20purpose%3F%20Well%2C%20if%20the%20expectation%20is%20performative%2C%20I%20see%20no%20issues%20with%20employees%20responding%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-workers-use-productivity-theater-performative-work-to-look-busy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperformative%20compliance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20encouragement%20to%20any%20employer%20who%20notices%20coffee%20badging%20happening%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EExplore%20the%20purpose%20of%20the%20expectation.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Do%20employees%20have%20a%20good%20reason%20to%20come%20to%20the%20office%20and%20stay%20there%3F%20Are%20they%20working%20on%20things%20that%20can%20be%20done%20better%20in%20person%3F%20Are%20they%20working%20side-by-side%20with%20managers%20or%20peers%20they%20can%20learn%20from%3F%20If%20not%2C%20then%20consider%20ways%20to%20make%20office%20time%20more%20purposeful%20to%20incentivize%20employees%20to%20not%20just%20show%20up%2C%20but%20stay.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFocus%20on%20results.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Look%20at%20data%20on%20productivity%20and%20outputs%20for%20teams.%20Are%20those%20in%20offices%20delivering%20stronger%20results%3F%20If%20so%2C%20that%20may%20help%20make%20a%20case%20for%20why%20they%20should%20be%20in%20office.%20But%20if%20there's%20no%20difference%20or%20they%20are%20more%20productive%20at%20home%2C%20then%20it%20may%20be%20time%20to%20drop%20that%20requirement.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETalk%20to%20your%20employees.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20you%20notice%20coffee%20badging%20happening%20in%20your%20business%2C%20talk%20to%20your%20people.%20Ask%20them%20why%20they%20are%20coming%20in%20for%20such%20a%20short%20time.%20They%20might%20have%20insights%20around%20barriers%20to%20productivity%20in%20the%20office%20so%20you%20can%20make%20changes%20that%20will%20help%20them%20be%20more%20present%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20more%20productive.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3ECoffee%20badging%20isn't%20a%20signal%20that%20employees%20are%20checked%20out%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-quiet-quitting-work-ethic-millennials-money-struggles-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitting%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20sign%20that%20employees%20simply%20do%20not%20see%20the%20need%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20to%20do%20their%20best%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20should%20either%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20make%20being%20in%20the%20office%20more%20purposeful%20%E2%80%94%20or%20drop%20that%20office%20requirement%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoffee-badging-crackdown-rto-rules-must-change-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusine