earby%20McDonald's%20drive-through%20and%20was%20on%20his%20way%20to%20see%20his%20girlfriend%20in%20Fulham%20when%20the%20crash%20took%20place.%20The%20accident%20happened%20at%20around%2010%3A06%20pm%20on%20March%2016%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutor%20Amanda%20Hilton%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BAs%20they%20came%20to%20traffic%20lights%2C%20Mr%20Williams%20pressed%20the%20button%20and%20looked%20to%20the%20right%20and%20the%20road%20was%20clear.%20They%20started%20crossing%20towards%20the%20central%20reservation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20they%20were%20crossing%2C%20Octavian%20Cadar%20drove%20his%20Mercedes%20after%20the%20roundabout%20at%20speed.%20They%20heard%20the%20car%20coming.%20Mr%20Williams%20ran%20on%20the%20journey%20they%20were%20taking.%20Charlotte%20ran%20back%20to%20the%20pavement%20they%20had%20just%20left%20and%20the%20Mercedes%20struck%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr%20Williams%2C%20who%20witnessed%20the%20collision%2C%20told%20police%20Charlotte%20was%20hit%20on%20the%20lefthand%20side%20by%20the%20bonnet%20of%20the%20car%20and%20he%20watched%20as%20Charlotte%20was%20thrown%20forward%20on%20to%20a%20railing.%20He%20heard%20her%20scream%20and%20then%20he%20saw%20her%20land%20on%20the%20ground.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722325980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fhj9ik7b8_vanessa-sagnay-de-la-bastida_625x300_30_July_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspeeding-driver-kills-ecuadorian-politicians-daughter-in-front-of-fiance-6221451%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vanessa%20Sagnay%20de%20la%20Bastida%2C%20daughter%20of%20an%20Ecuadorian%20politician%2C%20was%20tragically%20killed%20by%20a%20speeding%20Mercedes%20while%20crossing%20a%20road%20near%20Wandsworth%20Bridge%20in%20west%20London.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspeeding-driver-kills-ecuadorian-politicians-daughter-in-front-of-fiance-6221451%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspeeding-driver-kills-ecuadorian-politicians-daughter-in-front-of-fiance-6221451%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fspeeding-driver-kills-ecuadorian-politicians-daughter-in-front-of-fiance-6221451%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blog%3A%20Here's%20Why%20Jammu%20Is%20Seeing%20An%20Escalation%20In%20Terrorist%20Activities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Fjf09f4tg_jammu_625x300_30_July_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Army's%2028th%20Infantry%20Division%20was%20deployed%20in%20Kargil%20following%20the%20capture%20of%20Siachen%20by%20the%20Army.%20It%20was%20subsequently%20moved%20to%20Kupwara%20in%201991%20as%20militancy%20gripped%20the%20Valley.%20Nine%20years%20later%2C%20Pakistan%20captured%20the%20Kargil%20heights%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20Kargil%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%20Gorkha%20Hat%20and%20Maroon%20Beret%2C%20Lt%20Gen%20Chandra%20Shekar%20notes%20the%20decision%20to%20release%20the%2028th%20Infantry%20Division%20for%20deployment%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley.%20This%20involved%20removing%20dedicated%20reserves%20from%20the%20Ladakh%20sector%2C%20a%20necessity%20that%20was%20acutely%20felt%20during%20the%20Kargil%20War%20in%20May%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20large%20contingent%20of%20troops%20in%20Kashmir%20was%20redeployed%20to%20Kargil%2C%20contributing%20to%20India's%20victory%20in%20the%20conflict.%20The%20silver%20jubilee%20of%20this%20victory%20was%20observed%20on%20July%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Pakistan%20Exploited%20A%20Gap%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20following%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Kargil%20War%2C%20a%20security%20gap%20in%20the%20Kashmir%20Valley%20allowed%20Pakistan%20to%20deploy%20highly%20indoctrinated%20%3Cem%3Efidayeen%20%3C%2Fem%3E(suicide%20squads)%2C%20which%20significantly%20altered%20the%20nature%20of%20militancy%20in%20the%20region.%20The%20Valley%20experienced%20a%20surge%20in%20ruthless%20attacks%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20deaths%20of%20numerous%20security%20forces%2C%20civilians%2C%20and%20political%20leaders.%20This%20wave%20of%20violence%20was%20only%20mitigated%20when%20infiltration%20was%20largely%20halted%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20Army's%20fencing%20of%20the%20700%20km-long%20Line%20of%20Control%20and%20a%20ceasefire%20agreement%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20in%202003.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202020%2C%20after%20a%20deadly%20confrontation%20between%20the%20Indian%20and%20Chinese%20armies%20in%20Eastern%20Ladakh%2C%20the%20Army%20withdrew%20one%20division%20from%20the%20then-peaceful%20Pir%20Panjal%20region%20(Poonch%20and%20Rajouri%20districts)%20and%20redeployed%20it%20to%20Eastern%20Ladakh.%20This%20was%20part%20of%20a%20massive%20mobilization%20to%20match%20the%20number%20of%20Chinese%20troops%20stationed%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control.%20Early%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Army%20was%20compelled%20to%20redeploy%20a%20division%20to%20the%20now-troubled%20Pir%20Panjal%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20the%20post-Kargil%20situation%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20security%20gap%20in%20the%20Pir%20Panjal%20region%20was%20exploited%20by%20handlers%20in%20Pakistan.%20They%20began%20pushing%20highly%20trained%20militants%2C%20many%20believed%20to%20be%20Afghan%20war%20veterans%20and%20ex-Pakistani%20regulars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20October%202021%2C%20Pakistani%20militants%20had%20entrenched%20themselves%20in%20the%20forests%20of%20Poonch%20and%20Rajouri.%20They%20launched%20precise%20attacks%20on%20the%20army%2C%20causing%20casualties%20among%20troops%20while%20suffering%20few%20or%20no%20casualties%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20Kashmir%20To%20Jammu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spate%20of%20deadly%20attacks%20has%20now%20spread%20across%20the%20Jammu%20region.%20Recently%2C%20the%20Army%20had%20to%20deploy%20additional%20troops%20as%20districts%20like%20Kathua%2C%20Udhampur%2C%20Reasi%2C%20and%20Doda%20became%20as%20vulnerable%20as%20Pir%20Panjal.%20The%20government%20has%20also%20revamped%20civilian%20militias%2C%20known%20as%20Village%20Defense%20Guards%20(VDGs)%2C%20which%20now%20number%20around%2028%2C000%2C%20to%20defend%20against%20terrorist%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20why%20has%20the%20theatre%20of%20militancy%20shifted%20or%20expanded%20from%20the%20Valley%20to%20Jammu%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20security%20challenges%20on%20India's%20borders%2C%20military%20engagement%2C%20and%20militancy%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20are%20intertwined%2C%20local%20factors%20seem%20to%20have%20enabled%20a%20shift%20in%20militant%20strategy.%20Here's%20why...%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20long%20periods%20of%20militancy%2C%20the%20Valley%20acted%20as%20a%20buffer%2C%20insulating%20the%20Jammu%20region%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%20According%20to%20police%20records%2C%20over%2020%2C000%20militants%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20Kashmir%20over%20the%20last%20three%20decades.%20This%20includes%20hundreds%20of%20foreign%20militants%20from%2014%20different%20nationalities%2C%20who%20were%20pushed%20into%20the%20Valley%20to%20sustain%20the%20conflict.%20Effectively%2C%20the%20Valley%20absorbed%20these%20militants%20and%2C%20in%20the%20process%2C%20suffered%20greatly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20buffer%20in%20the%20Valley%20that%20once%20absorbed%20the%20brunt%20of%20Pakistan-sponsored%20insurgency%20has%20eroded.%20Pakistan%20no%20longer%20views%20Kashmiri%20mainstream%20leaders%20as%20Indian%20puppets.%20Instead%2C%20the%20dynamic%20has%20reversed%3B%20the%20government%20and%20ruling%20party%20frequently%20accuse%20regional%20leaders%20of%20fostering%20terrorism%20and%20separatism.%20Recently%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20police%20chief%20claimed%20that%20Pakistan%20has%20successfully%20infiltrated%20key%20sectors%20of%20civil%20society%20through%20mainstream%20and%20regional%20parties%20in%20the%20Valley%2C%20alleging%20that%20these%20parties%20have%20cultivated%20terrorist%20leaders%20for%20electoral%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Erosion%20Of%20The%20Mainstream%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20presence%20of%20local%20officials%20in%20bureaucracy%20and%20key%20police%20positions%20has%20diminished%20in%20significance.%20The%20Kashmiri%20mainstream%2C%20which%20once%20governed%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20has%20lost%20its%20political%20relevance%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20elected%20government%2C%20statehood%2C%20and%20a%20functioning%20electoral%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20former%20ruling%20class%20of%20Kashmir%20now%20resembling%20the%20ruled%2C%20Pakistan's%20perceptions%20of%20the%20Valley%20have%20shifted.%20Even%20the%20shutdown%20calls%20and%20notorious%20stone-pelting%20incidents%20previously%20were%20aimed%20to%20assert%20control%20between%20mainstream%20and%20separatists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20the%20buffer%20in%20Kashmir%20had%20insulated%20Delhi%20from%20blame.%20From%20the%20arrest%20of%20the%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Mohammad%20Abdullah%20in%201953%2C%20the%20dilution%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20semi-autonomous%20status%20in%201965%2C%20to%20the%20dismissal%20of%20the%20Farooq%20Abdullah%20government%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20in%201984%2C%20Delhi%20ensured%20that%20blame%20was%20directed%20away%20from%20itself.%20Instead%2C%20Kashmiri%20partners%20or%20collaborators%20were%20held%20accountable%20for%20issues%20in%20the%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20shifting%20the%20focus%20of%20militancy%2C%20Pakistan%20is%20turning%20Jammu%20into%20a%20powder%20keg%2C%20extending%20unrest%20up%20to%20the%20Punjab%20border.%20Besides%20attempts%20to%20incite%20communal%20strife%2C%20the%20goal%20appears%20to%20be%20to%20increase%20the%20cost%20of%20maintaining%20security%20while%20the%20Army%20faces%20challenges%20on%20two%20fronts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20BAT-type%20attack%20-%20a%20ruthless%20Pakistani%20military%20border%20action%20team%20assault%20-%20on%20an%20army%20post%20near%20the%20LOC%20in%20Kupwara%20is%20seen%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20escalate%20tensions%20at%20the%20borders.%20This%20attack%20occurred%20a%20day%20after%20India%20celebrated%20Kargil%20Vijay%20Diwas%2C%20during%20which%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20issued%20a%20stern%20warning%20to%20Pakistan%20over%20the%20spate%20of%20terrorist%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHighly%20Trained%20Militants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20three%20years%2C%20militants%20have%20established%20safe%20havens%20in%20the%20mountains%20of%20Jammu.%20They%20are%20trained%20in%20jungle%20warfare%2C%20and%20equipped%20with%20US-made%20M4%20carbines%20and%20steel-core%20bullets%20for%20targeting%20armored%20vehicles.%20For%20communication%2C%20they%20use%20encrypted%20state-of-the-art%20mini%20satellite%20systems%2C%20heavily%20protected%20against%20interception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20security%20forces%20are%20capable%20of%20handling%20militancy%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20primary%20challenge%20is%20the%20absence%20of%20credible%20human%20intelligence.%20In%20Kashmir%2C%20informers%20or%20'%3Cem%3Emukhbirs%3C%2Fem%3E'%20had%20long%20perfected%20the%20art%20of%20assisting%20security%20forces%20discreetly.%20Such%20channels%20are%20currently%20lacking%20in%20the%20Jammu%20region.%3Cbr%3E%5CnSince%20the%20buffer%20in%20Kashmir%20has%20eroded%2C%20there%20is%20silence%20in%20the%20Valley%20and%20violence%20in%20Jammu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Nazir%20Masoodi%20is%20NDTV's%20Srinagar%20Bureau%20Chief.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E